 flow, and also despite the large values of the film\nthickness based flow Reynolds number. When the characteristic Froude and Weber\nnumbers become significant, strong inertial effects influence the entrained\nliquid flux over the disc at large radius-to-immersion-depth ratio, namely via\nentrainment by the disc's lateral walls and via a contribution to the flow rate\nextracted from the 3D liquid sheet itself, respectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Mar 2020 17:27:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 15 Jul 2020 17:27:50 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 13 Oct 2020 18:49:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-15"}
